#!/usr/bin/env python3
# claude-lb-launch — launch Claude Code through agent-lb with sticky-session
# routing and a quota banner. Vendored, dependency-free (stdlib only).
#
# It claims a sticky account route from the load balancer, prints a one-line
# remaining-quota banner, then routes Claude Code through a local HTTPS proxy
# (HTTPS_PROXY): it MITMs api.anthropic.com -> the LB (injecting
# `x-claude-session-id`) and blind-tunnels every other host. Keeping Claude on
# the real api.anthropic.com with its keychain login is what lets Remote Control
# (/rc) stay enabled while still pooling accounts. The proxy streams SSE
# responses and dies with its parent.
#
# Usage:
#   clients/claude-lb-launch [claude args...]
#
# Env:
#   CLAUDE_LB_LOCAL_URL   local LB base URL, probed first (default http://127.0.0.1:2455)
#   CLAUDE_LB_LOCAL_PREFER=0  skip the local candidate; probe only CLAUDE_LB_BASE_URL
#                             (restores pre-federation single-URL behavior)
#   CLAUDE_LB_PREFER_REMOTE=1 probe CLAUDE_LB_BASE_URL first, then local as a fallback
#   CLAUDE_LB_BASE_URL   remote/fallback LB base URL (default http://127.0.0.1:2455)
#   CLAUDE_LB_DISABLE=1  bypass the LB entirely; exec plain `claude`
#   CLAUDE_LB_SESSION_ID stable session id (default cc-<pid>-<epoch>; headless
#                        -p/--print runs default to a stable cwd-derived id)
#   CLAUDE_LB_DRY_RUN=1  print the final command instead of exec'ing it
#   CLAUDE_LB_LAUNCHD_LABEL  local launchd job label (default com.aneyman.agent-lb)
#   CLAUDE_LB_STARTUP_GRACE_SECONDS  wait for a loaded local LB to become ready
#                                    after connection refusal (default 90; 0 disables)
#   CC_EFFORT_LEVEL      passed through as --effort
#   CC_PERMISSION_MODE   passed through as --permission-mode
#   NO_COLOR             disable the colored banner
#   CLAUDE_LB_WAIT_FOR_LIMIT      auto (default) waits for advertised limit
#                                 resets before launching; never disables
#   CLAUDE_LB_WAIT_MAX_SECONDS    cap on total waiting (default 21600 = 6h)
#   CLAUDE_LB_AUTO_RESUME         1 (default) auto-resumes headless (-p) runs
#                                 interrupted by account limits; 0 disables

